news.title: Sahara companies raised Rs 50,000 crore, did not pay back investors: SFIO
news.para: On October 31, 2018, the ministry of corporate affairs had assigned the probe to SFIO, which during the investigations found that Sahara India Commercial Corporation Ltd, Sahara India Financial Corporation Ltd and Sahara India Real Estate Corporation Ltd had collected Rs 14,100 crore, Rs 17,500 crore, and Rs 19,400 crore from public under the guise of different schemes promising higher returns to investors.

news.title: Over Rs one crore due, 600 families of Raheja Atharva in dark for five hours
news.para: According to residents, a temporary electricity connection was allowed by the Dakshin Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam (DHBVN), the discom, for the purpose of construction of the society earlier.

news.title: Oberoi Realty's profit rises 63% at Rs 467.53 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 846.19 crore during October-December period of this fiscal year from Rs 837.57 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: IMF warns China's property stress poses spillover risk
news.para: The International Monetary Fund's report comes as property firms in the world's second-biggest economy struggle with liquidity problems as Beijing looks to curb excessive debt and rampant consumer speculation in the sector.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body's committee to decide later on hike in user charges
news.para: The civic body had proposed that the user charge be raised from Re 1 per day to Rs 3 per day for residential properties and from Rs 2 to Rs 5 per day for commercial properties.

news.title: Britain to review buildings insurance cost rise after Grenfell fire
news.para: Britain's housing minister Michael Gove said on Friday the insurance market has been "failing" some leaseholders since the disaster, as insurance premiums have doubled year-on-year.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad development body to start next phase of demolition drive
news.para: The HDUDA has already demolished hundreds of illegal layouts in the first and second phase. Friday is the start of the third phase.

news.title: Century Plyboards India's net profit jumps 42.7% to Rs 93.9 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Its revenue from operations during October-December 2021 jumped 29.5 per cent to Rs 854.79 crore. It was Rs 660.09 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Embassy REIT's net operating income up 30% at Rs 621 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Embassy REIT leased 4,28,000 square feet across 15 deals, and achieved 14 per cent rent increases on 1.8 MSF. "Grew Net Operating Income ('NOI') by 30 per cent to Rs 621 crore, with operating margin of 84 per cent," the company said.

news.title: Surat: User charges hiked, no tax increase
news.para: Of the 1.54 lakh streetlights, 1.28 lakh have already been converted to LED while the remaining 26,605 will be converted this year.

news.title: Arvind Smartspaces' profit up 17% to Rs 5.91 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 44.93 crore during October-December period of this fiscal year from Rs 44.68 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: China's 2021 land sales slow sharply as property developers struggle
news.para: Revenue grew to 8.7 trillion yuan ($1.4 trillion), data from the finance ministry showed. The growth moderated from 3.8% for January-November, and compares with a 15.9% gain in 2020 and 11.4% in 2019.

news.title: In Dehradun, online property tax payment surpasses offline mode
news.para: The tax department of the Dehradun Municipal Corporation (DMC) has, so far, collected Rs 24 crore in property tax for this financial year. In contrast, the civic body had collected about Rs 17 crore in property tax till January 26 date last year.

news.title: Sebi to auction Ramel Industries' properties on Feb 24
news.para: Inviting bids for sale of properties in the recovery proceedings against Ramel Industries and its promoters or directors, Sebi said the e-auction will take place on February 24, 2022 between 10.30 am and 12.30 pm.

news.title: Nashik civic body slaps warrants to over 400 property tax defaulters
news.para: The civic body has given the tax defaulters a deadline of 21 days for paying the dues or they would face the action of confiscation of their properties. These defaulters have pending property tax dues for the past few years.
